    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for your contribution @kizdolf \r\n\r\nDid you try to use our [connectors](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/guide/Connectors.html) and more especially the [`connectHits` connector](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/connectors/connectHits.html)? \r\n\r\nI think you can achieve the behavior you want by using it like this: \r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport {connectHits} from 'react-instantsearch/connectors';\r\n\r\n<InstantSearch\r\n    appId=\"\"\r\n    apiKey=\"\"\r\n    indexName=\"\"\r\n>\r\n    <CustomHits indexName=\"\"/>\r\n</InstantSearch>;\r\n\r\nconst CustomHits = connectHits(props => {\r\n  const hits = props.hits.map(hit => <p>{hit.name}</p>);\r\n  return <div>\r\n    <p>Index used is : {props.indexName}</p>\r\n    {hits}\r\n  </div>;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you can see the `connectHits` connector has the `hits` props to display hits but you can also forward to it any props you want, so I added the `indexName` one. \r\n\r\nLet me know if this can solve your use case :) \r\n\r\n",
